<subSubSection id="C374652CFFB7FFDCD4CCFE38087CFDAD" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFB7FFDCD4CCFE38087CFDAD" blockId="74.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD4CCFE380C1AFE3E" bold="true" box="[199,322,403,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFB7FFDCD5B2FE380F03FE3E" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[441,603,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cofan" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD5B2FE380F03FE3E" box="[441,603,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Tenedos cofan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD66FFE380FFEFE3E" bold="true" box="[612,678,403,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFB7FFDCD66FFE380FFEFE3E" box="[612,678,403,429]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are characterized by shape of median apophysis (MA) with small sub-apical projection, small, complex retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA), forming concavity with irregular anterior edges; very short basal retrolateral tibial apophysis (bRTA), apically pointed (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD006FE7009C6FE65" box="[1037,1182,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[260,1325,194,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@76.[260,1327,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 52. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–D. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915):A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–D: 300µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520906/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Figs 52A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD0A1FE7009A7FE65" box="[1194,1279,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURE 53" captionStartId="77.[151,250,1642,1666]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,191,1606]" captionTargetId="figure-19@77.[151,1435,181,1618]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURE 53. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; CD, copulatory ducts; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles, St, subtegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520908/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">53A–B</figureCitation>
). Females are characterized by the epigyne provided with two anterolateral arches overhanging an oval medial field plate (MFP), and by short seminal receptacles (SR) curved towards median septum of epigyne (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD03BFD8809EFFDAD" box="[1072,1207,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[260,1325,194,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@76.[260,1327,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 52. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–D. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915):A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–D: 300µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520906/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Figs 52E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD0C9FD88084FFDAD" box="[1218,1303,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 53" captionStartId="77.[151,250,1642,1666]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,191,1606]" captionTargetId="figure-19@77.[151,1435,181,1618]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURE 53. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; CD, copulatory ducts; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles, St, subtegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520908/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">53C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFFB7FFDCD4CCFDEC0816F896" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFB7FFDCD4CCFDEC08CAFA9D" blockId="74.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD4CCFDEC0C01FDF2" bold="true" box="[199,345,583,609]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD56BFDEC0CC2FDF2" box="[352,410,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54D58805FFB7FFDCD5A3FDEC0F4DFDF2" box="[424,533,583,609]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-12317). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD76FFDEC0EB6FDF1" box="[868,1006,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="75.[151,250,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[268,1320,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@75.[268,1320,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURE 51. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (ICN-Ar-12915): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (ICN-Ar-12916): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520904/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 51A–B</figureCitation>
): carapace orange, dark brown in margins. Chelicerae with paturon brown, fangs brown-reddish. Endites light brown, white on anterior region. Labium and sternum light brown. Legs: Coxae I–IV pale yellow. Femora-tarsi I–IV brown. Abdomen: dorsally dark gray with five white guanine spots organized as follows: two irregular spots very close to each other with an anterior notch, anteriorly positioned; two sub-rounded spots larger than previous ones, anteromedially positioned; a transversal and wide band, posteriorly positioned. Lateral and ventrally pale beige without spots. Spinnerets light brown. Measurements: total length 3.65, carapace length 1.73, width 1.15, height 0.89. Clypeus height 0.33. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.07, ALE 0.09, PME 0.10, PLE 0.11; AME–AME 0.14, AME–ALE 0.16, AME–PME 0.25, PME–PME 0.20, PME–PLE 0.25, ALE–PLE 0.24. Chelicerae 0.68 length. Sternum length 0.77, width 0.75. Legs: I—femur 1.19/ patella 0.42/ tibia 1.33/ metatarsus 1.11/ tarsus 0.85/ total 4.90; II—1.08/ 0.44/ 0.89/ 0.90/ 0.82/ 4.13; III—1.05/ 0.48/ 0.63/ 0.68/ 0.64/ 3.48; IV—1.25/ 0.40/ 0.95/ 1.28/ 0.78/ 4.66. Abdomen length 1.62. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—metatarsus v1r-0-2; III—tibia v1p-1p-2, v2- 0-2; IV—metatarsus v2-1p-2. Palp: retrolateral process of cymbium (RPC) long, wider at base; tegulum (T) large, rounded, almost as long as wide, retrolateral excavation very accentuated; subtegulum (St) large, longer than wide; conductor (C) developed, wide, with short, very wide sclerotized region on distal side; appendix (ApC) short, apically sharp; embolus (E) long, filiform towards apex; base of embolus (EB) approximately as long as two times as basal tegular membrane; basal tegular membrane (BTM) originated proximally on tegulum, proximally flattened, ending as a very short appendix; spermatic ducts (SD) S-shaped thin with both folds full open; ventral tibial apophysis (VTA) short, quadrangular-shaped in ventral view; median apophysis (MA) large, squared with small projection on sub-distal side; retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) bifid, small, shorter than palpal tibia (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD09CFB58087EFA9D" box="[1175,1318,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[260,1325,194,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@76.[260,1327,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 52. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–D. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915):A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–D: 300µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520906/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Figs 52A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD13AFB5808DEFA9D" box="[1329,1414,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 53" captionStartId="77.[151,250,1642,1666]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,191,1606]" captionTargetId="figure-19@77.[151,1435,181,1618]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURE 53. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; CD, copulatory ducts; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles, St, subtegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520908/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">53A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFB7FFDCD4CCFABC08D7F971" blockId="74.[151,1437,259,1834]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD4CCFABC0C43FAA2" box="[199,283,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54D58805FFB7FFDCD520FABC0CCAFAA2" box="[299,402,1303,1329]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Paratype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-12916). Coloration and abdominal pattern of spots as male with the following exceptions: carapace uniformly brown, abdomen with two additional small spots, medially positioned, and spinnerets light yellow (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD555FAF40CB4FAE9" box="[350,492,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="75.[151,250,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[268,1320,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@75.[268,1320,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURE 51. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (ICN-Ar-12915): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (ICN-Ar-12916): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520904" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520904/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Fig. 51C–D</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 3.66, carapace length 1.68, width 1.08, height 0.74. Clypeus height 0.30. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.07, ALE 0.09, PME 0.09, PLE 0.08; AME–AME 0.08, AME–ALE 0.16, AME–PME 0.21, PME–PME 0.20, PME–PLE 0.25, ALE–PLE 0.26. Chelicerae 0.63 length. Sternum length 0.64, width 0.65. Legs: I—femur 0.82/ patella 0.47/ tibia 0.62/ metatarsus 0.64/ tarsus 0.67/ total 3.22; II—0.95/ 0.40/ 0.57/ 0.60/ 0.50/ 3.02; III—0.88/ 0.31/ 0.60/ 0.39/ 0.44/ 2.62; IV—1.06/ 0.31/ 0.70/ 0.77/ 0.63/ 3.47. Abdomen length 1.76. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—tibia v1-r-1r-2, metatarsus v1r-0-2; II—metatarsus v1r-0-2; III—metatarsus v2-0-2; IV—metatarsus v2-1p-2. Epigyne: lateral borders long and curved towards posteromedial region of epigyne, forming large, medial atrium with two anterolateral arches; median field plate large wider than long and oval-shaped; copulatory ducts very short, wide, almost undistinguished from spermathecae; seminal receptacles short, wide, curved towards median septum; spermathecae large, irregulars, posteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts almost as long as spermathecae length (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD090F96C087AF971" box="[1179,1314,1735,1762]" captionStart="FIGURE 52" captionStartId="76.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[260,1325,194,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@76.[260,1327,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURE 52. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–D. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915):A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–D: 300µm; E–F: 200µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520906" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520906/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Figs 52E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFB7FFDCD125F96C08DBF971" box="[1326,1411,1735,1762]" captionStart="FIGURE 53" captionStartId="77.[151,250,1642,1666]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,191,1606]" captionTargetId="figure-19@77.[151,1435,181,1618]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURE 53. Tenedos cofan sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12915): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-12916): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; CD, copulatory ducts; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles, St, subtegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520908" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520908/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">53C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFB7FFDCD4CCF9400816F896" blockId="74.[151,1437,259,1834]" box="[199,1358,1771,1798]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFB7FFDCD4CCF9400C67F896" bold="true" box="[199,319,1771,1797]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Variation.</emphasis>
Males (n=2): total length: 3.65–3.70; carapace length: 1.65–1.73; femur I length: 1.19–1.30.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
